qas.question: What style of architecture partially survived the war?
Southampton has been redeveloped almost entirely in the years since which war?
In which decade did there start to be a lot of traffic in Southampton?
Some of the walls around which landmark were demolished in the 1930s?

context: Pockets of <a0_0>Georgian<a0_0/> architecture survived the war, but much of the city was levelled. There has been extensive redevelopment since <a1_0>World War II<a1_0/>. Increasing traffic congestion in the <a2_0>1920s<a2_0/> led to partial demolition of medieval walls around <a3_0>the Bargate<a3_0/> in 1932 and 1938. However a large portion of those walls remain.
